The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, June 24, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Thursday, June 24, 2004				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Swami Vivekanandas statue in College Square to Park Street from 12 noon. Student activists of AIDSO will march in a procession.				 																																	Beltala at 11 am. Joint Council of Bus Syndicate meeting. 				 																Dance				 																																	Odissi dance by Shinjan Nrityalaya, Sambalpuri dance and Ghoda Nacha by artists from Orissa. At Swabhumi, 6 pm to 9 pm. 				 																Discussion				 																																	A seminar on Globalisation of Indian theatre to flag off ODEON 2004 theatre festival at Gharana, Oberoi Grand, 6.30 pm. Speakers include Manoj Mitra, Naseeruddin Shah, Nissar Allana and Anjan Dutt.				 																																	A consultation on Quality institutional care and alternatives for children organised by CRY and Praajak, at Peerless Inn from 10 am. 				 																Exhibition				 																																	Book display and docu-film show on Dum Dum Sekal Ekal will be inaugurated at 5.30 pm at 468/1, Jessore Road, Satgachhia-Jessore Road crossing.				 																																	Expressions, an exhibition of portraits by Vanesa Diaz, at Caffeine, 10 am to 3 pm and 5.30 pm to 11 pm.				 																Music				 																																	A music recital by Nupurchhanda Ghosh to mark the installation of Sri Aurobindos relics at Sri Aurobindo Institute of Culture, Regent Park, 6 pm.				 																Art beat				 																																	All-India paintings and sculptures at CIMA Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm. 				 																																	12th annual exhibition of Nijanta at Academy of Fine Arts, 3 pm to 8 pm.
